Example 2:

Input: nums = [-1,1,2]

Output: 3

Explanation:

​​​​​​​The average of nums is (-1 + 1 + 2) / 3 = 2 / 3 = 0.667.
The smallest absent positive integer greater than 0.667 is 3.©leetcode
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

class Solution {
    public int smallestAbsent(int[] nums) {
        HashSet<Integer> set= new HashSet<>();
        for(int i:nums){
            set.add(i);
        }
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        int sum=0;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            sum+=nums[i];
        }
        if(sum<0){
            sum=0;
        }
        int avg=sum/nums.length;
        int candidate= avg+1;
        while(true){
            if(!set.contains(candidate)){
                return candidate;
            }
            candidate++;
        }
    }
}
